
[1]famous

   FA'MOUS, a. [L. famosus. See Fame.]

   1. Celebrated in fame or public report; renowned; much talked of and
   praised; distinguished in story.

   Two hundred and fifty princes of the assembly, famous in the
   congregation. Num. 16.

   It is followed by for. One man is famous for erudition; another, for
   eloquence; and another, for military skill.

   2. sometimes in a bad sense; as a famous counterfeiter; a famous
   pirate.
